<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06219060 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06219060 </ACCESS><LEADPARA>  Toshiba America Information Systems Inc. on Monday introduced a 1-gigabyte 31/2-inch disk drive, which will be manufactured at a new plant in San Jose.The Irvine-based company said the drive will be used in work stations and fileserver computers. Analysts said Toshiba is among the first companies tointroduce a 1-gigabyte disk drive.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Business  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  TOSHIBA TO BUILD GIGABYTE DRIVES IN S.J.  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Financial Digest  </MEMO><BYLINE>  Mercury News Staff and Wire Reports  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910806  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Tuesday  </DAY><MONTH>  August  </MONTH><PG.COL>  3C  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  61  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Tuesday August 6, 199100219060,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>